### TITLE ###
ForOverUnionOfListsBindsUnionElement
### DESCRIPTION ###
Iterating a `int[]|str[]` should bind the loop var to `int|str`,
not Dynamic. Each arm contributes its element type and we union.
### INPUT ###
fn iter(xs: int[]|str[]):
    for v in xs:
        a = v
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  xs @ 2:14 -> int[]|str[]
  a @ 3:9 -> <no-type>
  v @ 3:13 -> int|str

# Symbol types
  a (local): int|str
  iter (fn): fn(int[]|str[]) -> void
  v (loop): int|str
  xs (param): int[]|str[]

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
ForOverUnionOfListsMismatchFires
### DESCRIPTION ###
Confirms the new union-of-lists binding flows into argument-type
checking: passing the loop var into a slot that admits only one
arm fires RAD30001.
### INPUT ###
fn iter(xs: int[]|str[]):
    for v in xs:
        consume(v)

fn consume(x: int):
    print(x)
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  xs @ 2:14 -> int[]|str[]
  consume @ 3:9 -> fn(int) -> void
  v @ 3:17 -> int|str
  print @ 6:5 -> dynamic
  x @ 6:11 -> int

# Symbol types
  consume (fn): fn(int) -> void
  iter (fn): fn(int[]|str[]) -> void
  v (loop): int|str
  x (param): int
  xs (param): int[]|str[]

# Diagnostics
  [hint] RAD30001 @ 3:17 - Argument type 'int|str' is not assignable to expected type 'int'
### TITLE ###
ForTwoVarOverMapBindsKeyAndValue
### DESCRIPTION ###
The two-var shape `for k, v in m` binds k to the map's key type
and v to its value type, matching the runtime's k/v iteration.
Mismatched downstream use fires on the value, not the key.
### INPUT ###
fn process(d: {str: int}):
    for k, v in d:
        consume_str(v)

fn consume_str(s: str):
    print(s)
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  d @ 2:17 -> { str: int }
  consume_str @ 3:9 -> fn(str) -> void
  v @ 3:21 -> int
  print @ 6:5 -> dynamic
  s @ 6:11 -> str

# Symbol types
  consume_str (fn): fn(str) -> void
  d (param): { str: int }
  process (fn): fn({ str: int }) -> void
  s (param): str
  v (loop): int

# Diagnostics
  [hint] RAD30001 @ 3:21 - Argument type 'int' is not assignable to expected type 'str'
### TITLE ###
ForTwoVarOverMapValueIsTyped
### DESCRIPTION ###
Confirms v is bound to the map's value type, not Dynamic. Locks
the type so a regression to the prior "second var unbound" shape
would surface.
### INPUT ###
fn process(d: {str: int}):
    for k, v in d:
        a = k
        b = v
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  d @ 2:17 -> { str: int }
  a @ 3:9 -> <no-type>
  k @ 3:13 -> str
  b @ 4:9 -> <no-type>
  v @ 4:13 -> int

# Symbol types
  a (local): str
  b (local): int
  d (param): { str: int }
  k (loop): str
  process (fn): fn({ str: int }) -> void
  v (loop): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
